  "text": "Prometheus implements web UI authentication through multiple mechanisms:\n\n## Admin API Access Control\nThe admin API access control is implemented directly in Prometheus at `web/api/v1/api.go`. The `API` struct contains an `enableAdmin` boolean field (line 241) that controls whether admin endpoints are accessible. Three admin endpoints are protected:\n- `/admin/tsdb/delete_series` - implemented in `deleteSeries()` function (line 2026), checks `!api.enableAdmin` (line 2027)\n- `/admin/tsdb/snapshot` - implemented in `snapshot()` function (line 2059), checks `!api.enableAdmin` (line 2060)\n- `/admin/tsdb/clean_tombstones` - implemented in `cleanTombstones()` function (line 2093), checks `!api.enableAdmin` (line 2094)\n\nThese endpoints are registered in the `Register()` function (lines 474-480). The `enableAdmin` flag is set via the `--web.enable-admin-api` command-line flag defined in `cmd/prometheus/main.go` (line 401-404).\n\n## BasicAuth Middleware and TLS Client Certificate Validation\nPrometheus delegates BasicAuth middleware and TLS client certificate validation to the exporter-toolkit library (`github.com/prometheus/exporter-toolkit/web`). These mechanisms are configured through the `--web.config.file` flag:\n\n1. In `cmd/prometheus/main.go` (lines 401-404): The `web.config.file` flag is defined as \"[EXPERIMENTAL] Path to configuration file that can enable TLS or authentication.\"\n\n2. Configuration validation in `cmd/prometheus/main.go` (line 1145): `toolkit_web.Validate(*webConfig)` validates the web configuration file.\n\n3. Configuration application in `web/web.go` (line 760): The `Handler.Run()` method calls `toolkit_web.ServeMultiple()` with the web config, which applies the authentication and TLS settings at the HTTP server level.\n\n4. In `cmd/promtool/main.go` (line 641): The `CheckWebConfig()` function uses `web.Validate(f)` to validate web configuration files.\n\nThe web configuration schema is documented in `docs/configuration/https.md`, which specifies:\n- `tls_server_config`: Configures TLS with `cert_file`, `key_file`, `client_auth_type`, and `client_ca_file` for TLS client certificate validation\n- `basic_auth_users`: Section for configuring BasicAuth with username-password pairs hashed with bcrypt\n- `http_server_config`: Additional HTTP headers and HTTP/2 configuration\n\nAn example configuration file is provided at `documentation/examples/web-config.yml`."
}

